# Frontend Component Standards

## React Component Structure

When creating React components:

```tsx
// 1. Imports at top
import React from "react";
import { ComponentProps } from "./types";

// 2. Interface definitions
interface ComponentProps {
  // Define props with proper typing
}

// 3. Component as named export
export function ComponentName({ prop1, prop2 }: ComponentProps) {
  // Component logic
  return <div className="tahoe-glass-container">{/* Component JSX */}</div>;
}
```

## Styling Guidelines

- **ONLY use Tailwind CSS** - no direct CSS styles
- Use Tahoe glass aesthetic with frosted glass styling
- Apply consistent spacing and typography
- Use semantic color classes for accessibility

## Tahoe Glass Styling Pattern

```tsx
// Standard Tahoe glass container
className =
  "bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-md border border-white/20 rounded-xl shadow-lg";

// Interactive elements
className = "hover:bg-white/20 transition-all duration-200";

// Form elements
className =
  "bg-white/5 border-white/10 focus:border-blue-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-400/20";
```

## Component Organization

- Place components in `frontend/src/components/`
- Use feature-based organization in `frontend/src/features/`
- Create reusable style components for common patterns
- Export types from separate `.ts` files

## State Management

- Use React hooks for local state
- Use context for global state
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Follow React best practices for performance

## Testing Requirements

- Write unit tests for all components
- Use React Testing Library
- Test user interactions and accessibility
- Maintain high test coverage
